*Duties
Communications:
• Lead communications and marketing for the School, leading the development of a comprehensive annual Marketing and Communication Strategy to be followed, and ensuring that these are effective in delivering noticeable success and traction with relevant audiences;
• Ensure the brand is prominent and adheres to agreed brand guidelines across all communication channels;
• Assist staff in the application of the School’s visual identity to their documents whether through providing guidelines or via developing templates, in association with Graphic Designer;
• Maintain databases of key stakeholders and manage regular communication via a variety of different media channels;
• Keep abreast of innovations in communications and marketing and recommend appropriate enhancements for implementation;
• Coordinate with the Graphic Designer appropriate digital and printed marketing materials consistent with the needs and
expectations of all stakeholders;
• Maintain stocks of marketing materials and equipment, ensuring that they are displayed at appropriate points throughout the School and available for events
• Maintain an up-to-date presence through the school’s website, relating to schools events and news.
• Ensure that noteworthy activities are communicated and/or celebrated to internal and external stakeholders and prospective
audiences, ensuring a sense of pride and satisfaction accordingly;
• Perform marketing research to find new opportunities and analysing market trends and conducting competitor research;
• Manage budgets for annual Marketing and Communication Plans;
• Design, manage, evaluate and analyze outcomes of marketing campaigns
• Collaborate closely with admissions team on a Lead Generation Plan that is transparent to all and effective.
• Update effective internal communication channels to inform students and faculty of school events, successes etc;
• Directing the school’s social media engagement strategy;
• To attend Marketing, Admissions and Communication Team meetings, liaising with senior school leaders for school success
stories, reporting on action plans and their effectiveness.

Written Communications and Press Releases
• Draft and edit press releases and school advertisements/advertorials, digital and print materials;
• Write interesting, creative, engaging and accurate articles for a range of audiences, liaising with the Copy Writer;
• Assist in the production of promotional materials and relevant communications for school events including, but not limited to, student academic/artistic exhibitions, music concerts;
• Assist with the creation of written resources to celebrate and promote the School’s unique history, ethos and educational
initiatives to prospective families, the wider community, societies and alumni;
• Research and place orders for suitable, branded, promotional items;
• Coordinate in the planning and organisation of promotional and recruitment events;
• Attend recruitment events and shows.
• Produce an advertising plan, including gathering information about audiences and rates for different options.
• Assist with the production of a School Year Book, Handbooks and school Profile, and other school publications.
Website and IT platforms:
• Management of the School website, with the relevant School Support and Services staff;
• Maintain an accurate Events Calendar for use by internal and external stakeholders;
• Liaise with to Head of School in maintaining an accurate Whole School Calendar;
• Inform Faculty staff of calendar changes, important messages and engaging content, including news, sport, events, videos and photographs.
• Utilise new media technologies to deliver website visitors and increase online visibility;
• Ensure all content is accurate and timely, working closely with the Copy Writer;
• Create, maintain and update video content for the School website on a regular basis;
• Create and maintain booking procedures and protocols for a range of events that take place throughout the year, produce email responses and maintain contact with future attendees;
• Ensure search engine optimization, in conjunction with the Website Manager;
• Maintain databases for, and content on, third party websites to ensure information is up-to-date and accurate at all times;
• Keep up-to-date with innovations in digital marketing and make recommendations, as appropriate;
• In conjunction with the copywriter, write and oversee the production of content that drives traffic to the school’s website;
• Work with all faculty staff to ensure that each department is represented appropriately to external stakeholders

Digital Marketing:
• Gather information for and then produce a range of weekly and periodic e-newsletters to stakeholders;
• Maintain a digital photographic library, including taking photos of School events and booking and organising professional
photography/videography, as required, in conjunction with the Events Coordinator;
• Determine the scope and quality of photographs required for promotional and communications use;
• Manage the School’s social media accounts, including maintaining the social media strategy and monitoring the School’s online presence;
• Produce monthly reports on effectiveness of social media posts
• Support academic staff with school social media advice/account management, carrying out training sessions, as appropriate.
Monitor staff content for appropriateness to school brand guidelines and policy;
• Produce e-invitations and use MailChimp and/or Outlook to send these to a maintained database
• Use the most appropriate tools for scheduling, tracking and producing digital communications;
• Use online survey software, such as Survey Monkey, to gather feedback on events and marketing activities, and send annual
surveys to key stakeholders;
